==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:L. Sprague de Camp|L. Sprague de Camp]].  

===Noun===
# According to L. Sprague de Camp, a credophile &ldquo; ...gets positive pleasure from belief and pain from doubt... The credophile collects beliefs the way a jackdaw does nest ornaments: not for utility but for glitter. And, once having embraced a belief, it takes something more than mere disproof to make him let go.&rdquo;
# Someone who is especially gullable.